  "commentary": "With SPX at 6825.49 sitting just below the massive +413M GEX wall at 6830, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while providing strong support around the 6817 flip line. The PIN regime with nearly 1B in total GEX creates a tight trading range, with dealers acting as stabilizers by selling rallies toward 6830-6840 and buying dips toward 6810-6817. The recent wall break event combined with the concentrated positive gamma between 6820-6830 suggests dealers will cap upside momentum while defending the downside.\n\nBottom line: expect price to stay pinned between 6817-6830 with limited breakout potential.",
